word_mean_info__list.difference: 指干预与自己毫不相关的事或不属于自己职责范围的事，隐含未经许可或授权。可与interfere换用。
书面用词，指介入争端，进行调停，也指干涉他人之事。
侧重指无权或未获允许而妨碍、阻扰、干涉他人之事。

bilingual.target: 不要干涉他们的个人事务。

bilingual.source: The noise can interfere with your concentration.
bilingual.target: 噪音会干涉你的注意力。

bilingual.source: Please do not interfere in my personal affairs.
bilingual.target: 请不要干涉我的个人事务。

bilingual.source: He tends to interfere with other people's work.
bilingual.target: 他倾向于干涉别人的工作。

bilingual.source: The government should not interfere in the free market.
bilingual.target: 政府不应该干涉自由市场。

bilingual.source: He always likes to interfere with other people's decisions.
bilingual.target: 他总是喜欢干涉别人的决定。

bilingual.source: She doesn't like it when people interfere in her decisions.
bilingual.target: 她不喜欢别人干涉她的决定。

bilingual.source: Parents should not interfere too much in their children's lives.
bilingual.target: 父母不应该过多干涉孩子的生活。

bilingual.source: Parents should not overly interfere with their children's choices.
bilingual.target: 父母不应该过多干涉孩子的选择。

bilingual.source: The government should not interfere with the freedom of the press.
bilingual.target: 政府不应该干涉媒体的自由。

yingyinNormal.zh: 永远不要干扰第一人称玩家射手。

yingyinNormal.en: You can only have two motives, Caroline, and I would interfere with either.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你们不过是有两个动机，但我不会妨碍到任何一个。

yingyinNormal.en: In turn, these tumors may interfere with the natural processes of the body, such as digestion and respiration, potentially leading to death.
yingyinNormal.zh: 接下来，这些肿瘤可能会干扰身体的自然活动，比如消化和呼吸，并可能导致死亡。

yingyinNormal.en: No, no, you guys do your experiments. I'll go pick up dinner. Are you sure? Yeah, you're having science fun, and I don't want to interfere, or watch you.
yingyinNormal.zh: 不不不，你们做实验吧。我去带晚饭回来。你确定吗？对啊，你们在享受科学，我不想打扰你们，也不想看。

examination_example.sentence: Newly launched satellites don't use radio frequencies that would <highlight>interfere</highlight> with existing satellites, and schedule when such new satellites can be launched.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 新发射的卫星不会使用干扰现有卫星的无线电频率，并会计划何时发射此类新卫星。

examination_example.sentence: The department will make sure that newly launched satellites don't use radio frequencies that would <highlight>interfere</highlight> with existing satellites.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 该部门将确保新发射的卫星不会使用干扰现有卫星的无线电频率。

examination_example.sentence: Our study will use a large corporate dataset to examine how technology extends our working hours and thus <highlight>interferes</highlight> with necessary cognitive recovery.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 我们的研究将使用一个大型企业数据集来研究技术如何延长我们的工作时间，从而干扰必要的认知恢复。

examination_example.sentence: Mental images often <highlight>interfere</highlight> with athletes performance.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 心理意象往往会影响运动员的表现。
